entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14276","n15540"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"head"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"head (enumerator for cattle)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leader, chief, chieftain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tip, top, summit, peak, upper part"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vertex, apex"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"extremity, end"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"promontory, headland, cape"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"main part"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beginning"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be at the head, to be chairman, to chair, to be in charge, to preside","examples":[{"text":"وَمِنْهُ ٱدِّعَاءُ أَوْلَادِ رَبَابٍ الْمَعْرُوفِينَ بِٱلْحِجَازِيِّينَ مِنْ بَنِي عَامِرٍ أَحَدِ شُعُوبِ زُغْبَةَ أَنَّهُمْ مِنْ بَنِي سُلَيْمٍ ثُمَّ مِنَ الشَّرِيدِ مِنْهُمْ، لَحِقَ جَدُّهُمْ بِبَنِي عَامِرٍ نَجَّارًا يَصْنَعُ الْحِرْجَانَ وَٱخْتَلَطَ بِهِمْ وَٱلْتَحَمَ بِنَسَبِهِمْ حَتَّى رَأَسَ عَلَيْهِمْ.","english":"The Awlad Rabab, who are known as the Hijazis and who belong to the Banu 'Amir, one of the branches of the Zughbah, claim that they belong to the Banu Sulaym and, in particular, to the Sharid, a branch of the Bani Sulaym. Their ancestor is said to have joined the Banu 'Amir as a carpenter who made biers. He mixed with them and developed a close contact with them. Finally, he became their leader."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to head, to lead, to direct, to manage, to run"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to appoint as the leader, to make the leader, director, chairman or president"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *raʔš-. Cognate with Akkadian 𒊕 (rēšum) and Biblical Hebrew רֹאשׁ (roʾš)."},"ipa":["/raʔs/","/ra.ʔa.sa/","/raʔ.ʔa.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14276","headword_ar":"رَاْسٌ","root":"rA^s","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Msb, K,) generally with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", except in the dial. of Benoo-Temeem, who constantly suppress the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man and of any animal;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain part of an animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) masc., (Msb, TA,) by common consent: (TA:) and (K) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"top,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K,) of a thing, (M,) or of anything; (A, K;) as, for instance, of a mountain, &c.; (the Lexicons, passim;) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley: (TA: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^isN","text_ar":"رَايِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl. (of pauc., S, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arow^usN","text_ar":"اَرْوُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and, by transposition,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=rusN","text_ar":"ا=رُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA, * [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aA^orusN","text_ar":"اَاْرُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the L, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^=ArAs","text_ar":"ا=اراس"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and (of mult., S, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^uwsu","text_ar":"رُوُوسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K, [by some carelessly written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^usN","text_ar":"رُوُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and by some, allowably,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^u=sN","text_ar":"رُوُ=سٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) which is not transposed, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwosN","text_ar":"رُوْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is elliptical. (M, TA.) A poet uses the pl. for the dual, saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"ruw^uwsu kabiyrayohin~a yanotaTiHaAni"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heads of the two great ones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old ones, of them, smite each other with their horns"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"اُمُّ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N","text_ar":"اُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alr~uw^uwsi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ الرُّوُوسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of the heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is applied by the people of Mekkeh to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the day called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Alqar~i","text_ar":"يَوْمُ القَرِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because then they eat the heads of the animals sacrificed. (A, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAba raA^osahu","text_ar":"اَصَابَ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kissed his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a metonymical phrase. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumiYa fulaAnN minohu fiY Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"رُمِىَ فُلَانٌ مِنْهُ فِى الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was shot by him in the head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he turned away from him, and did not look towards him nor pay any regard or attention to him, and deemed him troublesome."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumiytu minoka fiY Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"رُمِيتُ مِنْكَ فِى الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast an evil opinion of me"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that thou canst not look towards me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba raA^osahu","text_ar":"رَكِبَ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rkb","text_ar":"ركب"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladato waladahaA","text_ar":"وَلَدَتْ وَلَدَهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY raA^osK waAHidK","text_ar":"عَلَى رَاْسٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She brought forth her children one after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near after, another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M.) In like manner you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wulida lahu valaAvapu A^awolaAdK raA^osFA","text_ar":"وُلِدَ لَهُ ثَلَاثَةُ اَوْلَادٍ رَاْسًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY A_ivori raA^osK","text_ar":"عَلَى اـِثْرِ رَاْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osFA EalaY raA^osK","text_ar":"رَاْسًا عَلَى رَاْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had three children born to him one after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near after, another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijoEalo","text_ar":"اِجْعَلْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Al$~aYo'a raA^osFA waAHidFA","text_ar":"هٰذَا الشَّىْءَ رَاْسًا وَاحِدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make thou this thing to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISK, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA^j","text_ar":"باج"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodiY raA^osu mina Alganami","text_ar":"عِنْدِى رَاْسُ مِنَ الغَنَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have one head of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eid~apN mino","text_ar":"عِدَّةٌ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arow^usK","text_ar":"اَرْوُسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of head"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof]. (A, TA.) It is said in a trad. of' Omar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@joEaluwA Alr~aA^osa raA^osayoni","text_ar":"وَا@جْعَلُوا الرَّاْسَ رَاْسَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And make ye the one head two head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by buying two animals with the price of one, that, when one dies, the second may remain. (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frq","text_ar":"فرق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yarotabiTu ka*aA raA^osFA mina Ald~awaAb~i","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَرْتَبِطُ كَذَا رَاْسًا مِنَ الدَّوَابِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one ties so many head of beasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rbT","text_ar":"ربط"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTiniY raA^osFA mino vuwmK wa sin~FA minohu","text_ar":"اَعْطِنِى رَاْسًا مِنْ ثُومٍ وَ سِنًّا مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give thou to me a head of garlic, and a clove thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kamo fiY raA^osika mino sin~i","text_ar":"كَمْ فِى رَاْسِكَ مِنْ سِنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How many cloves are there in thy head"},{"kind":"text","text":"of garlic?]. (A, TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osN","text_ar":"رَاْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the end,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (MF. TA.) ―         -b11-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A head, head-land, cape,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"promontory."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b12-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hilt"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sword; (A;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^aAsN","text_ar":"رِيَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K; [in a copy of the A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaAsapN","text_ar":"رِيَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) or this signifies its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pommel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K,) more correctly; (Sgh;) and is also written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaAsN","text_ar":"رِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but whether for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^aAsN","text_ar":"رِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or originally with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is doubtful. (M.) [From the first of the above-mentioned significations arise several others, which are tropical. ―         -b13-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aA^osu waAl*~anabu","text_ar":"الرَّاْسُ وَالذَّنَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two nodes"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a planet: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tin~iynN","text_ar":"تِنِّينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b14-  Hence likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osN","text_ar":"رَاْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iysN","text_ar":"رَيِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà. (M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^uriyduhu raA^osFA","text_ar":"مَا اُرِيدُهُ رَاْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I do not desire him as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ry^ys","text_ar":"رييس"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head, chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu Alkufori","text_ar":"رَاْسُ الكُفْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino qibali Alma$oriqi","text_ar":"مِنْ قِبَلِ المَشْرِقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leader, of infidelity is from the direction of the place of sunrise"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: indicating that Ed-Dejjál or some other of the heads of error will come forth in the east. (TA.) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu AlmaAli","text_ar":"رَاْسُ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The capital,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"principal, of property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) [Hence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoraDatoniY Ea$arapF biraw^uwsihaA","text_ar":"اَقْرَضَتْنِى عَشَرَةً بِرَوُوسِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She lent me ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pieces of money]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a loan whereof the principal was to be repaid without interest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA. *) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaAfiyapu AlrA^osu Albayoti","text_ar":"القَافِيَةُ الراْسُ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rhyme is the principal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most essential, part of the verse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: said by one of the tribe of' Okeyl, to IJ. (M.) ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu Ald~iyni","text_ar":"رَاْسُ الدِّينِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxa$oyapu","text_ar":"الخَشْيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The principal part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beginning, of religion is fear"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God]. (A, TA.) ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu Al$~ahori","text_ar":"رَاْسُ الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beginning of the month."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu Als~anapi","text_ar":"رَاْسُ السَّنَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beginning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first day, of the year."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osu AlA^amori","text_ar":"رَاْسُ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^aAs","text_ar":"رِيَاس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK,) [both correct, as will be seen from what follows,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beginning of the affair; the first thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEido EalaY~a","text_ar":"اَعِدْ عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAmaka mino raA^osK","text_ar":"كَلَامَكَ مِنْ رَاْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"مِنَ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is less common, (M,) or is a vulgar phrase, not allowable, (S,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Repeat thou to me thy speech"},{"kind":"page_break","n":996},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the beginning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said by a person to one talking to him. (TA.) One also says to a person talking to him,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*ohu mino raA^osK","text_ar":"خُذْهُ مِنْ رَاْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou it from the beginning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b21-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota EalaYraA^osi A^amorika","text_ar":"اَنْتَ عَلَىرَاْسِ اَمْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY riy^aAsihi","text_ar":"على رِيَاسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art on the point of accomplishing thine affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota EalaY","text_ar":"اَنْتَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorika","text_ar":"اَمْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riy^aAsi","text_ar":"رِيَاسِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou art at the beginning of thine affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY raA^osi A^amorika","text_ar":"عَلَى رَاْسِ اَمْرِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b22-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraEato EalaY raA^osi Alwaladi","text_ar":"اَضْرَعَتْ عَلَى رَاْسِ الوَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DrE","text_ar":"ضرع"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b23-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`lika EalaY raA^osi fulaAnK","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلِكَ عَلَى رَاْسِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in the time of such a one; in his life-time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY rijoli fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَلَى رِجْلِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjl","text_ar":"رجل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b24-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osN","text_ar":"رَاْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A numerous and strong company of people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo raA^osN","text_ar":"هُمْ رَاْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are a numerous and strong company of people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo raA^osN EaZiymN","text_ar":"هُمْ رَاْسٌ عَظِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are an army by themselves, not needing any aid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) 'Amr Ibn-Kulthoom says, (S,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"biraA^osK mino baniY ju$ami boni bikorK\n                      \n                     \n                        naduq~u bihi Als~uhuwlapa waAlHuzuwnaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With a numerous and strong company of Benoo-Jusham-Ibn-Bekr, with which we beat the plains and the rugged tracts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M:) but [J says,] I think that he means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray^iys","text_ar":"رَيِيس"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head, chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] because he says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ndq~ bihi","text_ar":"ندقّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihimo","text_ar":"بِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","TA","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n15540","headword_ar":"رَاسٍ","root":"rsw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stationary, at rest, fixed, fast, firm, steady, steadfast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAlN raAsiyapN","text_ar":"جِبَالٌ رَاسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAsiyAatN","text_ar":"رَاسِياَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawaAsK","text_ar":"رَوَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Firm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"steadfast, mountains;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) the sing. of the last said by Akh to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAsiyapN","text_ar":"رَاسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidorN raAsiyapN","text_ar":"قِدْرٌ رَاسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cooking-pot that will not move from its place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of its greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that cannot be removed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quduwr raAsiyaAt","text_ar":"قُدُور رَاسِيَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur [xxxiv. 12] means, accord. to Fr, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cooking-pots that would not be lowered from their place, by reason of their greatness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}